  "description": [
    "KOREA TODAY A Book Review This 372page book only recently released is the first comprehensive study of the little country of Korea since its liberation and division The author is Dr George M McCune an outstanding American authority with a long personal knowledge of the country which is now the focal point of world conflict This book is scholarly analysis of Korea and the American and Russian occupation periods Reading the book we learn Korea shaped somewhat like Florida has area of 85000 square miles a little more than half as large as Montana Population is 29000000 or more than forty times larger than the popula tion of Montana It is a country with many tiny plains among predominat ing mountains It has fast flowing streams and 5400 miles of coast line with many good harbors the latter chiefly on the south and west coasts Korea lies in the north temp \u00e9r\u00e2t zone and has an annual though rather spotty rainfall much like that of eastern USA Mineral deposits a an in variable quantities include coal iron graphite tungsten zinc lead mercury magnasite molybdenum aluminum bearing ores and gold Ko rea has no oil Forests are found in the north"
  ],
